Reasoning: The paper proposes a framework for industrial information propagation and productisation using deep learning, specifically focusing on reverse-engineering and rebranding products. This involves image processing and manipulation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves aspects of cybersecurity and information theft, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of neural networks for this purpose also falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves searching for and manipulating information, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
